    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - REASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="11">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13016_13.xml" xrefid="f1301638">Figure 38</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate all parts prior to reassembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000
                Master Service Manual for recommended lubricants. Then install the pocket bearing to a depth of .070
                inch (1.8 mm) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301659">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301659" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301659" filename="../figg13/G1301659.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Install Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses when reassembling components.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st-reverse snap ring in the second groove from the bottom of the shaft. Slide
                the 1st-reverse collar into place and secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301660">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301660" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301660" filename="../figg13/G1301660.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Slide 1st-Reverse Collar Into Place</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the internally and externally splined thrust washers on the shaft. The internally
                splined thrust washer should rest against the snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301661">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301661" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301661" filename="../figg13/G1301661.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Place Thrust Washers on Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 2nd gear on the shaft. Install the externally and internally splined thrust washers
                into the gear. Secure the assembly with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301662">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301662" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301662" filename="../figg13/G1301662.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Install 2nd Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd clutch gear and snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301663">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301663" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301663" filename="../figg13/G1301663.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Install 2nd-3rd Clutch Gear and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place an internally splined washer and externally splined washer on the shaft. Install 3rd
                gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301664">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301664" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301664" filename="../figg13/G1301664.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Install 3rd Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the externally splined thrust washer, snap ring, and internally splined thrust washer
                into 4th gear. Place the assembly on the shaft. Secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301665">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301665" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301665" filename="../figg13/G1301665.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Place Thrust Washers and Snap Ring Into 4th Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fourth-fifth clutch gear and snap ring are installed next (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301666">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301666" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301666" filename="../figg13/G1301666.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Install 4th-5th Clutch Gear and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the externally splined thrust washer, snap ring, and internally splined thrust washer
                in the gear. Slide 5th gear onto the shaft. Secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301667">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301667" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301667" filename="../figg13/G1301667.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Slide 5th Gear onto Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the externally splined thrust washer, snap ring, and internally splined thrust washer
                in the gear. Slide 6th gear onto the shaft. Secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301668">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301668" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301668" filename="../figg13/G1301668.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Slide 6th Gear onto Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shaft on the bench. Install reverse gear. Butt 1st and reverse gears together and
                secure them with lockwire. This will provide the necessary clearance to install the mainshaft into the
                case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301669">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301669" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301669" filename="../figg13/G1301669.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Install Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
